# digest-runs/ holds the per-issue audit trail produced by the engineering-digest
# skill (candidates.json, run-plan.md, section-briefs.md, issue-N.html, issue-N.pdf,
# review.md). It is ignored by default because most local runs are test runs.
#
# When shipping a real issue:
#   - the published HTML/PDF goes to issues/issue-N.html and issues/issue-N.pdf
#     (these are tracked normally)
#   - the audit trail should be force-added: `git add -f digest-runs/issue-N/`
digest-runs/

# product-runs/ is the Product Edition's equivalent audit trail (product-digest
# skill). Same convention: ignored by default; the published HTML/PDF goes to
# product-issues/issue-N.html and product-issues/issue-N.pdf (tracked normally),
# and the audit trail for a shipped issue is force-added:
# `git add -f product-runs/issue-N/`
product-runs/

# Local-only tooling for PDF generation (puppeteer). Not part of the published site.
node_modules/
package.json
package-lock.json
